paragraph.value: The results, shown in Table 3, demonstrate that the MIMICK RNN recovers about half of the loss in performance incurred by the original Polyglot training model due to out-of-vocabulary words in the "All pairs" condition. MIMICK also outperforms VarEmbed. FastText can be considered an upper bound: with a vocabulary that is 25 times larger than the other models, it was missing words from only 44 pairs on this data.
